By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President of the 9th Senate, Ahmed Lawan on Saturday received the presidential flagbearer of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Ahmed Tinubu. Lawan, who pledged his unalloyed commitment as a loyal party member to work for the success of the party and our flag bearer at all times, reiterated that with Tinubu in the ballot, APC will go into the 2023 contest confident of victory. The Senate President disclosed this via series of tweets thus: “Earlier this evening, I received in audience, the presidential flag bearer of our great party, the APC, His Excellency, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu who came to my residence on a visit. “As I said to him in my congratulatory message, I have no doubt that with him on the ballot, our party will go into the 2023 contest confident of victory. “Again, I pledge my unalloyed commitment as a loyal party member to work for the success of the party and our flag bearer at all times”. Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu ABUJA - Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, has won All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential ticket for the 2023 general elections. Tinubu defeated 13 other contenders to emerge the flag bearer of the party at the Special National Convention of the party in Abuja on Wednesday. Details later (NAN) In "Top Stories" By PETER OKOLIE Governor Hope Uzodinma OWERRI- Gov. Hope Uzodinma of Imo on Friday,  congratulated Sen. Bola  Tinubu on his emergence as  presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) for the 2023 general election. Uzodinma  congratulated the APC Presidential flag bearer in a statement signed as the Chairman, APC… In "Politics" By OLUWATOPE LAWANSON Senator Tokunbo Abiru LAGOS- Sen. Tokunbo Abiru (APC – Lagos East )  says the All Progressives Congress (APC) made the best decision in choosing Sen. Bola Tinubu as its  2023 Presidential Candidate.Abiru  who congratulated Tinubu, a former Lagos State governor  on his emergence,  also said that APC… In "Politics"